extracted_text: D. Minimum lot size: For each single-family dwelling located on a pad, there shall be a lot area of not less than 4,000 square feet.
The total floor area of accessory structures more than 30 inches in height shall not exceed 30 percent of the area of the required rear yard.
llm_outputs.rationale: The section titled 'Area regulations' under the MH Mobile home-manufactured housing district regulations provides the maximum lot coverage by stating the minimum lot size and the percentage of the rear yard that can be covered by accessory structures.
